  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "WAREHOUSE ASSISTANT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Manage driver schedules for driver to delivery customers in the specific time and follow the given route plan</p>\n<p>• Verify the contents of inventory loads against shipping papers</p>\n<p>• Load and unload trucks, or vans</p>\n<p>• Obey traffic laws and follow established traffic and transportation procedures</p>\n<p>• Good service to customers</p>\n<p>• Update the ops team on daily out of stocks and provide daily feedback on pick-ups</p>\n<p>• Inspect and maintain vehicle supplies and equipment, such as gas, oil, water, tires, lights, or brakes, to ensure that vehicles are in proper working condition</p>\n<p>• Report any mechanical problems encountered with vehicles</p>\n<p>• Maintain records, such as vehicle logs, records of cargo, or billing statements, in accordance with regulations</p>\n<p>• Read maps and follow written or verbal geographic directions</p>\n<p>• Report delays, accidents, or other traffic and transportation situations to bases or other vehicles, using telephones or mobile two-way radios</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Class 3 driving license with 2 years minimum prior license issuance</p>\n<p>• 2 to 3 years’ experience in pick up, delivery. Pick up experience is an advantage</p>\n<p>• Presentable looking to meet customers on a day to day basis</p>\n<p>• Strong sense of pride and ownership in the work</p>\n<p>• Able to work independently and be part of a team</p>\n<p>• Self-motivated and thrives in a fast-growing and dynamic environment</p>\n<p>• Ability to deliver under tight deadline</p>\n<p>• Willingness to take on new challenges with a flexible, let's-give-it-a-try attitude</p>\n<p>• Responsible, organized with a good work attitude</p>\n<p>• Should be able to read and write English</p>\n<p><br></p>",
